with respect to operating processes and procedures can be
traced to ambiguities at higher levels owing to a short-
term approach to institutional funding and design. These
ambiguities percolate down through budgeting, hiring and
contracting procedures. These asymmetries are palpable
at multiple levels. At the scientific level, the variation of
attitudes among doctors and nursing staff is one such
asymmetry. At the level of human resource and staffing,
short-term contracts compounded by low pay and lacking
